  "prompt": "What\u2019s the industry average commission for a forex trader?",
  "response": "The industry average commission for forex trading can vary significantly based on several factors, including the broker, the type of account, and the services provided. Generally, many forex brokers operate on a spread basis rather than charging a direct commission. Spreads can range from 0.1 pips for major currency pairs with some brokers to several pips for less liquid pairs or with accounts that have no commissions.\n\nFor brokers that do charge a commission, it typically ranges from $5 to $15 per standard lot (100,000 units of currency) traded, depending on the broker's pricing structure and the account type. It's important to consider both spreads and commissions when evaluating the overall trading costs.\n\nDifferent brokers may offer various incentives or fee structures, so traders should compare different options and consider what best suits their trading style and frequency. Always check the specifics of any broker you contemplate using to understand their fee structure fully.",
